<paragraph id="8BC3369D1753AB65FCDE67409B9A1C5D" blockId="22.[842,1425,802,823]" box="[842,1425,802,823]" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">
<heading id="D08B81F11753AB65FCDE67409B9A1C5D" box="[842,1425,802,823]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" reason="2">
REMARKS ON 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1753AB65FC7F67409B291C5C" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" box="[1003,1314,802,823]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="626" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">SIMPLOMYS MEULENORUM</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1753AB65FAB867479B9A1C5D" bold="true" box="[1324,1425,802,823]" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41753AB65FAB867479B9A1C5D" box="[1324,1425,802,823]" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" rank="species">SP. NOV.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3369D1753AB65FCAE672B9A991B39" blockId="22.[826,1442,840,1902]" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">
In the localities of the Aragonian 
<typeStatus id="54C7883F1753AB65FB5D672B9AF11C34" box="[1225,1274,841,862]" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">type</typeStatus>
area, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1753AB65FADC672B9D931C16" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1753AB65FADC672B9D931C16" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">S. meulenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41753AB65FC3767059DF71C16" box="[931,1020,871,892]" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
does not show much morphological variation but does show morphological simplification of the m3. In the older localities of zone B, the m3 is already quite reduced and most specimens develop a single posterior ridge and full reduction of the posterior valley. In localities from the middle part of zone B until the end of zone C, only this completely reduced morphology is found.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3369D1753AB65FCC7603E9DFF1BA7" blockId="22.[826,1442,840,1902]" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">Ongoing research shows the presence of this species in the Ramblian. These assemblages will allow us to get a better understanding of the primitive character state of the m3.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3369D1753AB65FCC760B49DFA1804" blockId="22.[826,1442,840,1902]" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">
The m3 of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1753AB65FC4D60B59A821B81" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" box="[985,1161,1238,1260]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1753AB65FC4D60B59A821B81" box="[985,1161,1238,1260]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">S. meulenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41753AB65FB0160B59AE51B86" box="[1173,1262,1239,1260]" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1753AB65FABB60B59D8A1A60" baseAuthorityName="De Bruijn" baseAuthorityYear="1966" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simplicidens">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1753AB65FABB60B59D8A1A60" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">S. simplicidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the mesolophid and posterolophid fused into a single ridge, but this union is achieved in different ways in both species. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1753AB65FB5C61509B7C1A2D" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" box="[1224,1399,1330,1351]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1753AB65FB5C61509B7C1A2D" box="[1224,1399,1330,1351]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">S. meulenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41753AB65FA1561509D631A0C" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the mesolophid is almost completely reduced so the last ridge is mainly composed of the posterolophid (
<figureCitation id="13472A181753AB65FCD661EC9DBC1AC9" box="[834,951,1422,1444]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="15.[144,223,1414,1433]" captionTargetBox="[367,1201,195,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-165@15.[367,1201,195,1384]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 8. Simplomys meulenorum sp. nov. from Artesilla (collection MNCN). A, P4 ART-1142. B, M1 ART-874. C, M2 ART-882. D, M3 ART-1164. E, P4 ART-1227. F, M1 ART-873. G, M2 ART-886. H, M3 ART-1163. I, p4 ART-2498. J, m1 ART-901. K, m2 ART-910. L, m3 ART-1156. M, p4 ART-2499. N, m1 ART-894 holotype. O, m2 ART-918. P, m3 ART-1158. Right side specimens underlined. Holotype in italics." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443101/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">Fig. 8L, P</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1753AB65FC6561EC9AAA1AC9" baseAuthorityName="De Bruijn" baseAuthorityYear="1966" box="[1009,1185,1422,1443]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simplicidens">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1753AB65FC6561EC9AAA1AC9" box="[1009,1185,1422,1443]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">S. simplicidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the labial part of the mesolophid and the lingual part of the posterolophid are short as is shown in specimens with intermediate simplification; thus, the last ridge is equally composed of the lingual part of the mesolophid and the labial part of the posterolophid separated by an inflexion (
<figureCitation id="13472A181753AB65FC3B62279A0C1936" box="[943,1031,1605,1628]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[144,223,1374,1393]" captionTargetBox="[367,1201,195,1345]" captionTargetId="figure-201@11.[367,1201,195,1345]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Simplomys simplicidens (De Bruijn, 1966) from Valdemoros 3F (Fig. 4A–H) and Artesilla (Fig. 4I–P) (collection MNCN). A, P4 VA3F-27. B, M1 VA3F-39. C, M2 VA3F-52. D, M3 VA3F-62. E, p4 VA3F-342. F, m1 VA3F-73. G, m2 VA3F-76. H, m3 VA3F-95. I, P4 ART-1134. J, M1 ART-931. K, M2 ART-943. L, M3 ART-1173. M, p4 ART-2455. N, m1 ART-966. O, m2 ART-990. P, m3 ART-1186. Right side specimens underlined." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443085" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443085/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
). This inflexion is interpreted as a narrow trace of the posterior valley and is situated medially, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1753AB65FBB862E19AD319F2" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" box="[1068,1240,1667,1688]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1753AB65FBB862E19AD319F2" box="[1068,1240,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">S. meulenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41753AB65FB4B62E19B3F19F2" box="[1247,1332,1667,1688]" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
it is near the lingual border. Other morphological differences between the m3 of these species have been observed. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1753AB65FCCF62BD9A0C1999" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" box="[859,1031,1758,1780]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1753AB65FCCF62BD9A0C1999" box="[859,1031,1758,1780]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">S. meulenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41753AB65FB9B62BD9A6F199E" box="[1039,1124,1759,1780]" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the central valley is deeper than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1753AB65FC00629F9A4A1878" baseAuthorityName="De Bruijn" baseAuthorityYear="1966" box="[916,1089,1789,1810]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simplicidens">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1753AB65FC00629F9A4A1878" box="[916,1089,1789,1810]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">S. simplicidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1753AB65FBFA629F9B111878" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" box="[1134,1306,1789,1810]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1753AB65FBFA629F9B111878" box="[1134,1306,1789,1810]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">S. meulenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41753AB65FAB5629F9B7D1878" box="[1313,1398,1789,1810]" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the posterior part is lower than the anterior one and the posterior wall of the ridges is more inclined than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1753AB65FCAE633B9DE11804" baseAuthorityName="De Bruijn" baseAuthorityYear="1966" box="[826,1002,1881,1902]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="644" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simplicidens">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1753AB65FCAE633B9DE11804" box="[826,1002,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="644">S. simplicidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3369D1752AB64FF3C64A49F4D1E73" blockId="23.[144,759,198,1046]" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">
In the P4 of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1752AB64FEF064A49C881FB1" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" box="[356,643,198,219]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1752AB64FEF064A49C881FB1" box="[356,643,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">Simplomys meulenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41752AB64FD0264A49CFC1FB1" box="[662,759,198,219]" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the main cusps are less distinguishable than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1752AB64FF0465619F4B1E72" baseAuthorityName="De Bruijn" baseAuthorityYear="1966" box="[144,320,259,280]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simplicidens">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1752AB64FF0465619F4B1E72" box="[144,320,259,280]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">S. simplicidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3369D1752AB64FF3C65409C8B1D67" blockId="23.[144,759,198,1046]" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">
An unusual morphological feature in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1752AB64FDE365409CDF1E52" authorityName="MUIRHEAD" authorityYear="1819" box="[631,724,290,312]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Gliridae</taxonomicName>
is found in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1752AB64FE9365239FB71E3F" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" box="[263,444,320,342]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1752AB64FE9365239FB71E3F" box="[263,444,320,342]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">S. meulenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41752AB64FE5865239C221E3C" box="[460,553,321,342]" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
In the M1, the anteroloph may be interrupted and connected medially to the protoloph (
<figureCitation id="13472A181752AB64FE19651F9C091EF9" box="[397,514,381,403]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="15.[144,223,1414,1433]" captionTargetBox="[367,1201,195,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-165@15.[367,1201,195,1384]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 8. Simplomys meulenorum sp. nov. from Artesilla (collection MNCN). A, P4 ART-1142. B, M1 ART-874. C, M2 ART-882. D, M3 ART-1164. E, P4 ART-1227. F, M1 ART-873. G, M2 ART-886. H, M3 ART-1163. I, p4 ART-2498. J, m1 ART-901. K, m2 ART-910. L, m3 ART-1156. M, p4 ART-2499. N, m1 ART-894 holotype. O, m2 ART-918. P, m3 ART-1158. Right side specimens underlined. Holotype in italics." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443101/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">Fig. 8B, F</figureCitation>
). The taxonomical or functional value of this particular morphology is not clear, but it is present in half of the M1 of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1752AB64FD1F65D99ED01E85" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1752AB64FD1F65D99ED01E85" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">S. meulenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41752AB64FF7765B89F311E85" box="[227,314,474,495]" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from all localities, whereas it is much less common in the M1 of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1752AB64FE5D659A9C721D67" baseAuthorityName="De Bruijn" baseAuthorityYear="1966" box="[457,633,504,525]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simplicidens">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1752AB64FE5D659A9C721D67" box="[457,633,504,525]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">S. simplicidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3369D1752AB64FF3C66749CEC1DCC" blockId="23.[144,759,198,1046]" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1752AB64FF3C66749FCE1D41" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" box="[168,453,534,555]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1752AB64FF3C66749FCE1D41" box="[168,453,534,555]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">Simplomys meulenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41752AB64FE4266759C3F1D46" box="[470,564,535,556]" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1752AB64FDEB66759EDC1D20" baseAuthorityName="De Bruijn" baseAuthorityYear="1966" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simplicidens">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1752AB64FDEB66759EDC1D20" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">S. simplicidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
show statistically significant differences in length, width, and surface for all dental elements when these two species occur in the same locality (Table 4); 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1752AB64FE9066F39FB81DCC" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" box="[260,435,657,678]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1752AB64FE9066F39FB81DCC" box="[260,435,657,678]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">S. meulenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41752AB64FE2966F39C1F1DCC" box="[445,532,657,678]" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the larger one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3369D1752AB64FF3C66CD9C511C34" blockId="23.[144,759,198,1046]" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1752AB64FF3C66CD9FCB1DAE" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" box="[168,448,687,708]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1752AB64FF3C66CD9FCB1DAE" box="[168,448,687,708]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">Simplomys meulenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41752AB64FE5F66D29C2F1DAF" box="[459,548,688,709]" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shows a trend to size increase through time in the studied area (
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B6C1752AB64FF03668F9F981C69" author="Garcia-Paredes I" box="[151,403,749,771]" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" refId="ref17607" refString="Garcia-Paredes I. 2006. Patrones evolutivos de los Gliridae (Rodentia, Mammalia) del Mioceno inferior y medio del area tipo del Aragoniense (Cuenca de Calatayud - Montalban). Unpublished D. Phil. Thesis, Universidad Complutense de Madrid." type="book" year="2006">García-Paredes, 2006</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation id="13472A181752AB64FE3A668F9FF41C69" box="[430,511,749,771]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1792,1811]" captionTargetBox="[198,1368,1026,1762]" captionTargetId="graphics-199@17.[236,1368,1028,1741]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 10. Temporal distribution of average surface of the upper and lower cheek teeth in species of Simplomys gen. nov. from the Aragonian type area (Calatayud–Montalbán basin, Spain). Only localities with at least five measurable specimens of each element are included. Horizontal bars represent two times the standard deviation. Modified after García-Paredes, 2006." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443107/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). As a result of this trend, size ranges of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1752AB64FE0E676E9C451C4A" authority="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra, 2009" authorityName="García-Paredes &amp; Peláez-Campomanes &amp; Álvarez-Sierra" authorityYear="2009" box="[410,590,779,801]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meulenorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1752AB64FE0E676E9C451C4A" box="[410,590,779,801]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">S. meulenorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23B57F41752AB64FDC8676E9CB31C4B" box="[604,696,780,801]" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
may overlap with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1752AB64FEA367489FCB1C55" authorityName="De Bruijn" authorityYear="1967" box="[311,448,810,831]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Pseudodryomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="645" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1752AB64FEA367489FCB1C55" box="[311,448,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="645">S. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, different morphologies allow us to distinguish them.
</paragraph>
